id: pm-u83w
title: pm install writes absolute-home-path into tracked .managed-extensions.json
description: "When `pm install calendar` runs, the project-scope managed-extensions.json gets `source.input/location` absolute paths like ~/<repo>/packages/pm-calendar. These leak local home paths into a tracked file and break secret scans. Built-in packages bundled with pm-cli should be persisted by package-name reference (or repo-relative path), not absolute filesystem location."
type: Issue
status: open
priority: 1
tags[5]: agent-ux,extensions,packages,pm-cli,privacy
created_at: "2026-05-16T21:56:54.403Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-16T21:56:54.403Z"
author: maintainer-agent
acceptance_criteria: "pm install <builtin-name> persists source as {kind: 'builtin', name: ...} or relative-to-repo path; secret scan no longer flags managed-extensions.json after install; teams can share extension setup via committed tracker."
parent: pm-rnpb
body: ""
